1
00:00:08,203 --> 00:00:10,703
I came in here and
the room was empty

2
00:00:11,484 --> 00:00:13,281
And they flogged me here

3
00:00:14,219 --> 00:00:18,020
They made me stand up, and I was wearing
trousers then, or rather <i>sirwal</i>

4
00:00:18,698 --> 00:00:20,729
And a sweater. He
made me take it off

5
00:00:20,754 --> 00:00:22,161
And he flogged me here

6
00:00:23,385 --> 00:00:28,515
He tells you, while flogging, Ask your Lord
for forgiveness, ask God for forgiveness

7
00:00:29,609 --> 00:00:31,458
Interviewer: How was your
posture? Were you standing upright?

8
00:00:31,483 --> 00:00:32,604
Yes, I was standing right here

9
00:00:33,672 --> 00:00:37,292
And wearing the <i>sirwal</i>,
and my sweater was off

10
00:00:37,656 --> 00:00:39,531
And he lashed my
back with their whip

11
00:00:40,859 --> 00:00:41,953
Interviewer: And your hands?

12
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:45,166
My hands were like this, forward

13
00:00:49,932 --> 00:00:51,390
Interviewer: How many
people were in this room?

14
00:00:51,415 --> 00:00:53,447
No one, just me and the flogger

15
00:00:56,468 --> 00:01:00,973
These things weren’t
here—this was an empty room

16
00:01:01,598 --> 00:01:07,457
The ISIS flogger brought
me in and made me stand

17
00:01:08,030 --> 00:01:09,671
And he started flogging

18
00:01:15,296 --> 00:01:19,619
Interviewer: Do you think they
did this to get information from you?

19
00:01:20,505 --> 00:01:23,968
It was flogging for
punishment only

20
00:01:25,028 --> 00:01:32,267
If they wanted information from
someone, they’d take it from him

21
00:01:33,048 --> 00:01:35,965
I mean, he doesn’t beat you
to make you say this or that

22
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:38,309
He flogs for the ID
issue, just 100 lashes

23
00:01:40,574 --> 00:01:44,715
Interviewer: What type of
torture was common in this prison?

24
00:01:45,757 --> 00:01:48,283
I was only flogged; I
don’t know about the rest

25
00:01:49,481 --> 00:01:55,912
And this isn’t their only
prison—they have many prisons

26
00:01:55,937 --> 00:01:58,595
Across various <i>Hisba</i> bases—not just this one

27
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:03,205
There was Badush
Prison, which held detainees

28
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:07,423
And Mosul Tasfirat
Prison also had detainees

29
00:02:07,865 --> 00:02:09,974
But this was a <i>Hisba</i> base

30
00:02:11,908 --> 00:02:18,210
Interviewer: Was there <i>sukhra</i> [forced
labor] or did they order you to clean?

31
00:02:18,235 --> 00:02:19,304
Inside the prison?

32
00:02:19,329 --> 00:02:20,449
No, there wasn’t

33
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:23,783
I mean, they don’t throw trash

34
00:02:23,808 --> 00:02:26,231
And tell you, come
and clean the trash

35
00:02:26,751 --> 00:02:27,949
It wasn’t like that

36
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:34,251
Interviewer: What instrument
did he use to flog you?

37
00:02:35,788 --> 00:02:38,861
Their flogging whip is a stick

38
00:02:39,772 --> 00:02:43,314
With leather strips
like belt leather

39
00:02:44,173 --> 00:02:45,710
And he flogs

40
00:02:47,012 --> 00:02:49,095
Until it leaves a real
mark on the back

41
00:03:00,943 --> 00:03:05,761
Interviewer: Did the flogger insult you
or use obscene words while flogging?

42
00:03:05,786 --> 00:03:09,797
The flogger only stood, flogged, and
told me—Ask your Lord for forgiveness

43
00:03:12,271 --> 00:03:13,730
He only says—Ask
your Lord for forgiveness

44
00:03:15,214 --> 00:03:19,094
Interviewer: Was there sympathy
for the prisoners inside the cell?

45
00:03:19,119 --> 00:03:21,776
You mean among
the prisoners, or how?

46
00:03:21,801 --> 00:03:25,162
Interviewer: I mean, was there sympathy
from the ISIS member toward you?

47
00:03:25,187 --> 00:03:27,636
No, he sympathized with no one

48
00:03:28,521 --> 00:03:32,661
Only the washbasins
issue, as I said, that’s all

49
00:03:36,021 --> 00:03:40,266
Interviewer: Could you hear the prisoners’
voices while they were being tortured?

50
00:03:42,635 --> 00:03:50,057
I didn’t hear, but the torture
places existed, not in this place

51
00:03:50,943 --> 00:03:56,021
I didn't see a torture room, but
there were dedicated rooms for torture

52
00:03:58,365 --> 00:04:03,156
If someone was charged with a serious offense,
they took him elsewhere and tortured him

53
00:04:03,181 --> 00:04:04,797
Not inside this place

54
00:04:05,214 --> 00:04:07,662
Only minor charges
were handled here

55
00:04:08,209 --> 00:04:10,006
The light detention was here

56
00:04:10,605 --> 00:04:14,146
But anyone with a serious charge was
taken to another place, another prison

57
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:16,516
He was transferred to
another prison immediately

58
00:04:16,821 --> 00:04:18,462
Interviewer: What about women?

59
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:20,649
I didn't see any women here

60
00:04:21,951 --> 00:04:24,451
I mean, I didn't see
female prisoners here

61
00:04:28,957 --> 00:04:36,196
Interviewer: The one who tortured or
flogged you—what was his nationality?

62
00:04:36,795 --> 00:04:38,280
I don't know his nationality

63
00:04:38,305 --> 00:04:42,628
But it's clear he was Iraqi

64
00:04:42,941 --> 00:04:44,607
From his speech, it's
obvious he was Iraqi

65
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:48,879
Most of them are from
villages and rural areas

66
00:04:49,164 --> 00:04:51,743
Those areas are outside
Mosul, not inside it

67
00:04:55,511 --> 00:04:59,183
Interviewer: Was there any
prisoner who was with you

68
00:05:00,042 --> 00:05:03,844
Whom they took out for flogging
and then brought back to the cell?

69
00:05:04,131 --> 00:05:07,073
No. As I told you, when they flog
someone, they remove him afterward

70
00:05:20,615 --> 00:05:27,918
Interviewer: Did the flogging
leave a physical mark on you?

71
00:05:27,943 --> 00:05:31,460
Of course. Someone hits you
on your back with 100 lashes

72
00:05:31,981 --> 00:05:34,559
I suffered with my
back for about a week

73
00:05:35,705 --> 00:05:38,231
My back stayed red for a week

74
00:05:38,621 --> 00:05:42,762
I used treatments and
ointments until the pain eased a bit

75
00:05:45,705 --> 00:05:48,491
The flogged area is
obvious—its color is red

76
00:05:49,298 --> 00:05:52,709
When anyone is hit with a
water hose or something else

77
00:05:52,734 --> 00:05:54,637
The beating marks will appear

78
00:05:55,001 --> 00:05:57,423
They stayed for about
a week or ten days

79
00:05:58,283 --> 00:06:00,001
I couldn't sleep on my back

80
00:06:01,043 --> 00:06:02,241
I slept on my stomach

81
00:06:03,882 --> 00:06:06,356
Interviewer: What's
the story of your illness?

82
00:06:07,267 --> 00:06:11,043
And what was the main cause?

83
00:06:11,068 --> 00:06:15,314
When ISIS entered, I was
working with transport trucks

84
00:06:15,887 --> 00:06:18,413
When they came in, I
could no longer work

85
00:06:19,481 --> 00:06:22,761
I got older, but
not just from age

86
00:06:22,786 --> 00:06:24,220
Livelihood was unavailable

87
00:06:24,376 --> 00:06:26,876
I'm responsible for ten people

88
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:29,741
Because of that, I fell ill

89
00:06:30,184 --> 00:06:31,954
I developed
cirrhosis of the liver

90
00:06:31,979 --> 00:06:34,949
My lungs are fatigued

91
00:06:34,974 --> 00:06:36,824
And the kidneys too

92
00:06:36,849 --> 00:06:38,595
I underwent
catheterization twice

93
00:06:39,168 --> 00:06:44,142
My blood sugar level reaches 600

94
00:06:44,897 --> 00:06:47,241
And cataracts affected my eyes

95
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:50,809
I had surgery on one eye, and
the other still needs an operation

96
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,386
Thank God in every circumstance

97
00:06:54,662 --> 00:06:57,318
Because of ISIS I
contracted all these diseases

98
00:06:57,343 --> 00:06:59,375
I used to work, and after they
came I stayed home for a long time

99
00:07:00,053 --> 00:07:01,563
There was no work

100
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,959
I was forced to
work as a taxi driver

101
00:07:05,495 --> 00:07:08,438
I had to work as a
taxi driver for a while.

102
00:07:08,776 --> 00:07:10,964
After the liberation,

103
00:07:11,563 --> 00:07:14,167
I got sick, so I couldn’t get
back to working on trucks.

104
00:07:14,192 --> 00:07:15,834
Because my line of
work is transport trucks.

105
00:07:17,084 --> 00:07:18,594
Thank God.
